1
00:00:40,067 --> 00:00:42,300
<i>Perhaps, you don't need
to resign?</i>

2
00:00:42,433 --> 00:00:43,833
<i> I needed space, remember?</i>

3
00:00:43,967 --> 00:00:45,800
<i>I'm sure that's
what mom wanted too.</i>

4
00:00:45,933 --> 00:00:47,067
<i> That's not true.</i>

5
00:00:47,200 --> 00:00:49,000
<i>Mommy Pretty misses you so much.</i>

6
00:00:49,133 --> 00:00:49,933
<i> Jeffrey?</i>

7
00:00:50,067 --> 00:00:51,833
<i> He didn't go to work today.</i>

8
00:00:51,967 --> 00:00:53,267
<i> Looks like he has resigned.</i>

9
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:55,167
<i>I thought they wouldn't
let personal issues</i>

10
00:00:55,300 --> 00:00:55,967
<i> affect their job.</i>

11
00:00:56,100 --> 00:00:57,267
<i> I'm sorry, Andrea.</i>

12
00:00:57,400 --> 00:00:59,733
<i>I was hoping that your anger
would subside.</i>

13
00:00:59,867 --> 00:01:01,900
<i>I blamed myself
so many times before.</i>

14
00:01:02,033 --> 00:01:03,833
<i>Because if I hadn't gotten sick,
you wouldn't have left.</i>

15
00:01:03,967 --> 00:01:05,133
<i>You wouldn't have
met that woman.</i>

16
00:01:05,267 --> 00:01:06,733
<i> You wouldn't have left us.</i>

17
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:08,400
<i> Dear, don't blame yourself.</i>

18
00:01:08,533 --> 00:01:09,733
<i> You did nothing wrong.</i>

19
00:01:09,867 --> 00:01:11,033
<i> I'm here now.</i>

20
00:01:11,167 --> 00:01:12,867
<i> Let me make it up to you.</i>

21
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:15,367
<i>Let me be a father to you again.</i>

22
00:01:15,500 --> 00:01:17,600
<i>I don't even know
how to be your child anymore.</i>

23
00:01:17,733 --> 00:01:20,867
<i>You should have thought it
through before talking to her!</i>

24
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:22,567
<i> Felma, that's all I can do!</i>

25
00:01:22,700 --> 00:01:24,633
<i>Because I'm stuck
in this wheelchair!</i>

26
00:01:24,767 --> 00:01:26,400
<i>Do you have any idea
how hard it is</i>

27
00:01:26,533 --> 00:01:28,933
<i>not being able to do anything
for you and our children?</i>

28
00:01:29,067 --> 00:01:31,200
<i>Dear, we just want
to talk to you.</i>

29
00:01:31,333 --> 00:01:33,600
<i>Maybe it's better
if we talk in the van.</i>

30
00:01:33,733 --> 00:01:35,200
<i> Mister, start the van now!</i>

31
00:01:35,333 --> 00:01:37,667
<i> I didn't agree to this!</i>

32
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:39,167
<i>- Jessica?
- Shut up!</i>

33
00:01:43,833 --> 00:01:46,433
Here, Mrs. Flores,
have a cup of tea.

34
00:01:46,567 --> 00:01:48,867
I didn't come here to have tea.

35
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:53,000
What I need is for the stocks
to be delivered to my store!

36
00:01:53,133 --> 00:01:56,833
What now? You made me wait
all day for nothing?

37
00:01:56,967 --> 00:01:59,167
I've been calling Andrea,
and what?

38
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:01,867
She's not answering my calls!

39
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:06,167
Ma'am, the moment I confirm
that you're fully paid,

40
00:02:06,300 --> 00:02:08,800
I'll have the products
delivered immediately.

41
00:02:08,933 --> 00:02:10,767
It's already paid!

42
00:02:10,900 --> 00:02:13,067
I paid for that
in advance last week!

43
00:02:14,433 --> 00:02:16,300
Where's Andrea?

44
00:02:16,433 --> 00:02:18,600
Ma'am, I haven't been
able to reach her.

45
00:02:18,733 --> 00:02:20,200
I'll send her a text.

46
00:02:20,333 --> 00:02:21,300
Seriously.

47
00:02:21,433 --> 00:02:23,867
So what now? You're going
to make me wait here?

48
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:25,000
What about my store?

49
00:02:25,133 --> 00:02:26,900
It's been waiting for the stocks
to be delivered.

50
00:02:27,033 --> 00:02:28,033
Is this right?

51
00:02:28,167 --> 00:02:29,367
Making your client
wait like this?

52
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:30,100
Ma'am, I'm sorry, but...

53
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:31,467
Mrs. Flores.

54
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:32,567
Hello, Ma'am.

55
00:02:34,900 --> 00:02:36,333
Finally, Andrea.

56
00:02:36,467 --> 00:02:38,900
Where have you been?

57
00:02:39,033 --> 00:02:41,167
I just had a little delay.

58
00:02:41,300 --> 00:02:42,433
Because I had an emergency.

59
00:02:42,567 --> 00:02:45,267
But I'm here now.

60
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:48,200
Aunt, I have all the receipts.

61
00:02:48,367 --> 00:02:50,967
Everything's good.

62
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:55,233
The products Mrs. Flores
ordered are fully paid for.

63
00:02:55,367 --> 00:02:57,900
We will deliver the products as
soon as possible, Mrs. Flores.

64
00:02:58,033 --> 00:03:00,067
You better make sure you
deliver that today, okay?

65
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:01,133
Yes, Ma'am.

66
00:03:01,267 --> 00:03:03,600
Have a great day!

67
00:03:03,733 --> 00:03:06,100
Auntie, I'll give you
the copy, okay?

68
00:03:06,233 --> 00:03:07,700
And then these files.

69
00:03:07,833 --> 00:03:08,967
- I'll endorse these
- Hello?

70
00:03:09,100 --> 00:03:10,767
- to the secretary, okay?
- I'm looking for Miss Andrea.

71
00:03:16,533 --> 00:03:17,600
Joel?

72
00:03:22,233 --> 00:03:23,667
What are you doing here?

73
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:29,867
I'm sorry, Mommy.

74
00:03:32,600 --> 00:03:34,267
I'm choosing to stay.

75
00:03:36,867 --> 00:03:40,533
You're choosing that mistress
over me, your real mom?

76
00:03:42,100 --> 00:03:42,900
Go ahead then!

77
00:03:43,033 --> 00:03:44,500
Stay with her!

78
00:03:44,633 --> 00:03:47,167
But I promise you, Felma.

79
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:48,067
This is not over yet!

80
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:49,233
We will settle this!

81
00:03:49,367 --> 00:03:51,967
And I'll make sure I win!

82
00:04:02,133 --> 00:04:05,333
I'm in the area, so I thought
I would stop by your office.

83
00:04:05,467 --> 00:04:08,133
I'm glad you have time to
have some coffee with me.

84
00:04:08,267 --> 00:04:11,633
I have to meet someone too.

85
00:04:11,767 --> 00:04:13,767
Is that why you have
luggage with you?

86
00:04:17,533 --> 00:04:18,567
What about you?

87
00:04:18,700 --> 00:04:21,033
I'm glad you have time
for a coffee break.

88
00:04:21,167 --> 00:04:22,400
What do you do for
a living anyway?

89
00:04:29,133 --> 00:04:30,500
Here.

90
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:37,900
Real estate?

91
00:04:38,033 --> 00:04:38,900
Yes.

92
00:04:39,033 --> 00:04:41,233
I have some condo units
for lease.

93
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,533
Excuse me, I have
to take this call.

94
00:04:47,667 --> 00:04:49,000
Okay.

95
00:04:49,133 --> 00:04:51,200
Hello, Jeffrey?

96
00:04:51,333 --> 00:04:52,633
How are you doing?

97
00:04:52,767 --> 00:04:54,500
Have you already
found an apartment?

98
00:04:54,633 --> 00:04:56,633
Not yet.

99
00:04:56,767 --> 00:04:59,200
I told you,
you can stay with us.

100
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:00,933
You can squeeze in with us.

101
00:05:01,100 --> 00:05:02,433
I told you already,
it's embarrassing,

102
00:05:02,567 --> 00:05:04,400
especially to Daisy.

103
00:05:04,533 --> 00:05:06,700
Neither of us has a job
right now.

104
00:05:06,833 --> 00:05:08,500
I'll find a place
of my own soon.

105
00:05:08,633 --> 00:05:10,133
Fine.

106
00:05:10,267 --> 00:05:12,333
But if you don't find
a place today...

107
00:05:12,467 --> 00:05:13,967
I mean today...

108
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:15,867
Come here. You can stay with us.

109
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:20,800
Okay, I get it.

110
00:05:20,933 --> 00:05:22,067
I have to go.
I'm with someone right now.

111
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:23,300
Okay, bye.

112
00:05:37,100 --> 00:05:40,767
So you're leasing some
of your condos?

113
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:44,300
Can I be your tenant?

114
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:52,533
That stubborn child!

115
00:05:52,667 --> 00:05:55,167
I was begging her.

116
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:56,967
I was so close
to getting down on my knees.

117
00:05:58,267 --> 00:06:01,167
And still she didn't choose me.

118
00:06:01,300 --> 00:06:05,233
She chose to go with
that darn Felma instead.

119
00:06:05,367 --> 00:06:07,967
So your threat didn't work?

120
00:06:08,133 --> 00:06:10,300
It's your...

121
00:06:10,433 --> 00:06:13,200
Well, it's your lawyer's fault!

122
00:06:13,333 --> 00:06:14,233
He's too righteous.

123
00:06:14,367 --> 00:06:16,367
He sticks to the rules.

124
00:06:16,500 --> 00:06:20,033
I paid a lot of money for
his service, but he's useless!

125
00:06:20,167 --> 00:06:21,500
Well, at least he agreed
to do it

126
00:06:21,633 --> 00:06:22,933
when I told him you were just
going to threaten them.

127
00:06:23,067 --> 00:06:25,600
Not all lawyers
would agree to that.

128
00:06:26,667 --> 00:06:32,233
The question is, did Felma fall
for my threat?

129
00:06:32,367 --> 00:06:34,933
Because if she didn't,
then it's no use.

130
00:06:35,067 --> 00:06:38,333
Because she'll never
give Manuel up.

131
00:06:38,467 --> 00:06:40,767
Why don't you try bashing her
online again?

132
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:43,267
Like what you did before.

133
00:06:43,433 --> 00:06:46,400
If you ruin her reputation,

134
00:06:46,533 --> 00:06:48,200
she won't have a choice
but to give them up.

135
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:51,600
I don't want to do that!

136
00:06:51,733 --> 00:06:52,967
I don't want to get exposed
like that anymore.

137
00:06:54,733 --> 00:06:56,600
I don't want people to see me.

138
00:06:56,733 --> 00:07:01,133
Friend, you don't need
to expose yourself.

139
00:07:01,267 --> 00:07:04,633
You know, we can contact
that one famous vlogger,

140
00:07:04,767 --> 00:07:06,800
Karla Talakera.

141
00:07:06,933 --> 00:07:08,433
I've been following her.

142
00:07:08,567 --> 00:07:12,367
We'll use her to
get Felma exposed.

143
00:07:14,167 --> 00:07:15,867
I won't be seen in the video?

144
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:17,567
No.

145
00:07:17,700 --> 00:07:22,200
Then you better make sure
that Felma will be ruined.

146
00:07:31,333 --> 00:07:33,667
Felma, thank you for bringing
my daughter back.

147
00:07:33,900 --> 00:07:36,567
But there's still trouble,
Manuel.

148
00:07:36,700 --> 00:07:40,033
Hazel threatened to sue us.

149
00:07:41,700 --> 00:07:45,567
She wouldn't go through
with it if I went with her.

150
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:49,600
But Dad, I can't bear
for us to be apart.

151
00:07:49,767 --> 00:07:52,500
I'm so sorry, Aunt Felma.

152
00:07:52,633 --> 00:07:54,333
Dear, you did the right thing.

153
00:07:54,467 --> 00:07:57,567
And it's for your own safety.

154
00:07:57,833 --> 00:08:02,500
But, Dad, what if her mom
goes through with her threat?

155
00:08:02,633 --> 00:08:04,600
I don't want you and
mom to go to jail.

156
00:08:06,967 --> 00:08:09,200
Sweetie, that will never happen.

157
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:12,433
We won't go to jail.

158
00:08:12,567 --> 00:08:15,233
We will fight for what is right.

159
00:08:16,933 --> 00:08:19,767
Dad, I'll fight with you.

160
00:08:19,900 --> 00:08:23,267
As long as we're together,
everything will be okay.

161
00:08:33,233 --> 00:08:34,200
Come in.

162
00:08:36,800 --> 00:08:37,967
Go.

163
00:08:44,767 --> 00:08:51,433
This one is 40 square meters,
one bedroom.

164
00:08:51,567 --> 00:08:53,733
It's spacious, well-maintained,

165
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:57,667
and it also has a generator
in case the power goes out.

166
00:08:57,800 --> 00:09:00,233
And if you want...

167
00:09:00,367 --> 00:09:01,600
Come here.

168
00:09:01,733 --> 00:09:05,300
Here's the bedroom. I have one
more unit in the other wing.

169
00:09:05,433 --> 00:09:06,700
It has two bedrooms.

170
00:09:08,900 --> 00:09:11,433
No, this is good enough.

171
00:09:11,567 --> 00:09:13,467
So, how much is the rent?

172
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:17,267
Thirty thousand, including
association fees.

173
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:19,767
Oh, it's pricey.

174
00:09:19,900 --> 00:09:21,900
How much for the deposit
and advance payment?

175
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:25,467
You can move in without that.

176
00:09:28,333 --> 00:09:30,733
You can't do that, Joel.

177
00:09:31,033 --> 00:09:33,200
I don't want special favors.

178
00:09:33,333 --> 00:09:34,900
I don't want to be
indebted to anyone.

179
00:09:35,033 --> 00:09:37,567
Andrea, I just want
to help you out.

180
00:09:37,700 --> 00:09:39,900
You could use your money
for something else.

181
00:09:41,733 --> 00:09:46,833
If you need anything,
food or someone to talk to,

182
00:09:46,967 --> 00:09:49,000
just let me know.

183
00:09:49,133 --> 00:09:50,967
Okay. Thank you.

184
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:52,067
Anytime.

185
00:09:58,367 --> 00:10:00,067
You know what?

186
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:01,567
I'll take this.

187
00:10:12,033 --> 00:10:15,133
I already contacted
Karla Talakera.

188
00:10:15,267 --> 00:10:16,900
I hope she responds soon.

189
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:32,633
So, you're serious about
getting a job here?

190
00:10:32,767 --> 00:10:33,733
I need to.

191
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,300
Looks like I'm going to
stay here for a while.

192
00:10:40,167 --> 00:10:43,633
It's hard to take my family back
from Felma.

193
00:10:46,467 --> 00:10:49,167
Wait, what about your properties
in Canada?

194
00:10:52,100 --> 00:10:53,767
I don't know.

195
00:10:53,900 --> 00:10:55,133
Whatever happens, happens.

196
00:10:55,267 --> 00:10:59,000
Maybe I'll just sell them
or rent them out

197
00:10:59,133 --> 00:11:01,333
to earn something.

198
00:11:01,467 --> 00:11:02,833
Yeah, just rent them out.

199
00:11:02,967 --> 00:11:04,600
So you'll still have
something to come back to.

200
00:11:07,767 --> 00:11:09,833
By the way,
how was the job hunting?

201
00:11:12,667 --> 00:11:14,700
That's another problem.

202
00:11:14,833 --> 00:11:17,167
Nothing.

203
00:11:17,300 --> 00:11:18,967
All are rejections.

204
00:11:19,100 --> 00:11:20,067
Look at that.

205
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:32,700
It's so hard.

206
00:11:34,333 --> 00:11:37,000
Every job I applied to
says I'm overqualified.

207
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:43,967
It's true, though.

208
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:45,933
You're qualified
to be a head nurse.

209
00:11:46,067 --> 00:11:48,400
Or even a nurse manager.

210
00:11:56,100 --> 00:11:58,533
Who's this?

211
00:11:58,667 --> 00:11:59,633
It's just a phone number.

212
00:12:02,900 --> 00:12:04,100
Hello?

213
00:12:04,233 --> 00:12:06,633
You unimaginable witch!

214
00:12:06,767 --> 00:12:09,567
So you're back
in the Philippines?

215
00:12:09,700 --> 00:12:12,267
Excuse me, who's this?

216
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:16,267
Your number one nemesis
at San Au Uni.

217
00:12:16,433 --> 00:12:21,733
You took my throne
at the College of Nursing!

218
00:12:21,867 --> 00:12:24,267
Myla Andrada?

219
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:25,867
Miles, is that you?

220
00:12:27,633 --> 00:12:29,700
The one and only!

221
00:12:29,833 --> 00:12:32,533
So what's up?
How are you, you litle devil?

222
00:12:32,667 --> 00:12:34,200
Well, I'm still prettier
than you.

223
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:37,733
Whatever. You're insane.

224
00:12:37,867 --> 00:12:39,667
How did you get my number?

225
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:40,667
<i> Hello!</i>

226
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:42,867
You listed it online.

227
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,433
Wait a minute.
What are you up to?

228
00:12:44,567 --> 00:12:45,867
Are you staying here for good?

229
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:49,133
Oh, well, testing the waters.

230
00:12:49,300 --> 00:12:51,367
I'm actually job hunting
right now.

231
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:54,267
You might know
where I can get one.

232
00:12:54,400 --> 00:12:56,167
<i> Are you still a nurse?</i>

233
00:12:56,300 --> 00:12:57,467
Well, of course I am.

234
00:12:57,600 --> 00:12:58,333
You know me.

235
00:12:58,467 --> 00:13:00,067
I'm not just any nurse.

236
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:01,767
I'm the nurse manager.

237
00:13:01,900 --> 00:13:03,033
See?

238
00:13:03,167 --> 00:13:05,200
I beat you for a change.

239
00:13:05,333 --> 00:13:07,433
You're just a senior nurse,
right?

240
00:13:07,567 --> 00:13:10,800
And I'm a nurse manager.

241
00:13:10,933 --> 00:13:12,367
Well, excuse me.

242
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:13,533
I was a senior nurse in Canada.

243
00:13:13,667 --> 00:13:15,733
International level.

244
00:13:15,867 --> 00:13:18,333
<i> Oh wow, am I getting to you?</i>

245
00:13:18,467 --> 00:13:20,233
Still won't back down?

246
00:13:20,367 --> 00:13:21,233
Okay, fine.

247
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:24,000
Send me your resumé.

248
00:13:24,133 --> 00:13:25,433
I'll pass it along to HR.

249
00:13:25,567 --> 00:13:26,667
<i> Really?</i>

250
00:13:26,800 --> 00:13:28,000
Oh wow, thank you.

251
00:13:28,133 --> 00:13:29,400
I will do that!

252
00:13:29,533 --> 00:13:30,700
You're welcome.

253
00:13:30,833 --> 00:13:32,700
Wait. I have to go,
there's an emergency.

254
00:13:32,833 --> 00:13:35,433
Okay, I'll just text
you my email address.

255
00:13:35,567 --> 00:13:37,400
Send me your CV, okay?

256
00:13:37,533 --> 00:13:38,533
<i> I'll make sure of that.</i>

257
00:13:38,667 --> 00:13:39,833
Thank you so much.

258
00:13:39,967 --> 00:13:41,067
See you soon!

259
00:13:44,567 --> 00:13:47,900
So, who's Miles?

260
00:13:48,033 --> 00:13:50,700
She's my sorority sister
from college.

261
